Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.86,0:00:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Inherited will...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The tide of the times... People's dreams...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.41,0:00:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These things cannot be stopped.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.20,0:00:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As long as people seek the answer of freedom,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.29,0:00:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}these things will never cease to be!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:42.02,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:47.52,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,hashitteru jounetsu ga anata o kiramekaseru
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.52,0:00:53.53,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.53,0:00:57.03,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.33,0:01:03.71,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka o
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:06.98,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,oikakete oikaketeku
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.98,0:01:10.27,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,doramatikku te ni ireru made
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.18,0:01:22.33,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,dare ni mo mienai yume no katachi o
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:25.39,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.39,0:01:31.40,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui kimochi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:34.49,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,tsujitsuma awase betsu ni iranai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:37.84,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,arifureta nichijou yori mo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:41.08,OP2-Romaji,,0,0,0,,paradaisu mezashite hashire
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:42.02,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I only believe in the future, I don't care if anyone laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:47.52,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,that racing passion makes you shine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.52,0:00:53.53,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,it's too bright, but I want to gaze at it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.53,0:00:57.03,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,I sense "aesthetics" somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.33,0:01:03.71,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,I follow, follow in the footsteps of a dream
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:06.98,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,that resembles no one
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.98,0:01:10.27,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,until I dramatically get it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.18,0:01:22.33,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to catch, catch the shape
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:25.39,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,of a dream no one can see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.39,0:01:31.40,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:34.49,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,I don't really need everything to add up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:37.84,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:41.08,OP2-English,,0,0,0,,run for paradise instead
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.13,0:01:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We found an island!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.88,0:01:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,An island?!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.18,0:01:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! An island! We found an island!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.72,0:02:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Nami! Good for you! \NThere's an island! You can get better!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.60,0:02:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an island! An island! Island!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.85,0:02:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,– Island! Island!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.02,0:02:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,– Just go look.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.15,0:02:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,An island!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.40,0:02:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All this snow! I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.83,0:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's far enough, pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.33,0:02:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. I found people.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.67,0:02:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But... they don't seem too friendly...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.38,0:02:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention, pirates! \NLeave this place at once! This instant!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.76,0:02:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to find a doctor!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.18,0:02:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a sick person onboard!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.47,0:02:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't fall for that trick, you filthy pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.48,0:02:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They really hate our guts. \NAnd we've just met, too...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.69,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk back!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.32,0:02:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They're shooting!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.90,0:02:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't just do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.78,0:02:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,– Bastard!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.78,0:02:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,– Stop, Sanji-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:18.63,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,2000)\pos(346.5,100)}An Island Without Doctors?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:18.63,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,2000)\pos(357.5,405)\fsp-2.5)}Adventure in a Nameless Land!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.55,0:03:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.05,0:03:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you...!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.64,0:03:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Aim!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.57,0:03:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.36,0:03:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighting won't help anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.28,0:03:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine! It only grazed my arm!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.83,0:03:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, we won't land here! \NBut could we ask for a doctor?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.87,0:03:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our friend is suffering from a grave illness. \NPlease help! I beg you!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.59,0:03:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.59,0:04:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not fit to be captain, Luffy.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.05,0:04:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everything can be fixed by acting recklessly!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.72,0:04:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start a fight here, \Nwhat will happen to Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.32,0:04:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm sorry! I was wrong!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.74,0:04:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please call a doctor!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.95,0:04:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help our friend!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.72,0:04:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I will show you to the village.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.47,0:04:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.19,0:04:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See? They understood!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! You're amazing!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.62,0:05:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I must warn you, the only \Ndoctor we have here is a witch.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.38,0:05:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Witch?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.00,0:05:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta be kidding me. \NNothing here makes sense...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.63,0:05:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this place, anyway?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.97,0:05:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This land still does not have a name.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.22,0:05:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A nameless land? \NDoes that really happen?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.15,0:05:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A bear!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.23,0:05:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone! Pretend to be dead!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.61,0:05:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A Hiking Bear. They pose no danger.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.41,0:05:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget to bow. \NIt's proper hiking manners.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.58,0:05:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! All better now!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.29,0:05:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.50,0:06:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can finally do some real training!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.76,0:06:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I was getting sick of that watered-down training,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.43,0:06:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and just watching the ship is boring as hell.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.64,0:06:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll go for some cold-weather \Nswimming to suppress my self.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.56,0:06:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our village, Big Horn.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.07,0:06:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There are weird animals walking everywhere...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.45,0:06:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's snow country for ya!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.53,0:06:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}! \NWe made it to a village with people! It's a village!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thanks for the help, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.12,0:06:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who aren't guards can return to their work.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.00,0:06:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But, will you be alright by yourself, Dalton-{\i1}san{\i0}? \NThey're pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.08,0:06:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe they pose no threat.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.75,0:06:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my hunch of many years of experience. \NYou can trust it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.34,0:06:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.55,0:06:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what Dalton-{\i1}san{\i0} says, then...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.14,0:06:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't {\i1}seem{\i0} dangerous...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.35,0:06:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.60,0:07:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, Dalton-{\i1}san{\i0}! \NWe leave the rest to you!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.31,0:07:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Be ever careful, Dalton-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.15,0:07:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just call us again if anything happens!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.36,0:07:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't this land's security forces?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.53,0:07:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're ordinary citizens.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.82,0:07:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to my home for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.41,0:07:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Look, Luffy! A Hiking Bear!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.95,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Again?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.00,0:07:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Dalton-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.25,0:07:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta bow.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.45,0:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard there were pirates! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.83,0:07:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, everything is okay. \NThere's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.76,0:07:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Dalton-{\i1}kun{\i0}! \NI look forward to the election in two days!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.96,0:07:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says they're going to vote for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.60,0:07:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You can't be serious! \NI'm nothing but a sinful man!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.73,0:07:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Use that bed there. \NI'll warm the place up.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.61,0:07:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't told you my name yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.28,0:07:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dalton, captain of the \Nsecurity squad of this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.45,0:08:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive our heavy-handed welcome.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.71,0:08:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,May I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.83,0:08:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.71,0:08:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I somehow feel like I've seen you before.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.88,0:08:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's probably just your imagination!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.46,0:08:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, please tell us about this witch!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.01,0:08:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}'s temperature was 42°C \Nwhen I checked it just now!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.60,0:08:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,42°?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.73,0:08:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Her fever's gone up for three days in a row.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.69,0:08:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll die if it goes up any more!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.40,0:08:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.40,0:08:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't even know the cause of \Nher illness, or how to treat it...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.03,0:08:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We need a doctor! Anyone will do! \NWhere is this witch of yours?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.17,0:08:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The witch, huh. Do you see those \Nmountains outside the window?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.70,0:08:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those insanely tall-
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.62,0:08:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyper Snowman!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.75,0:08:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Snowzilla, the snow beast!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.17,0:08:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.34,0:08:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me kick your asses!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.18,0:08:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those mountains are known \Nas the Drum Rockies.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.35,0:09:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see the castle at the top \Nof the tallest one in the middle?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.39,0:09:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Castle?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.27,0:09:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That castle no longer has its king.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.10,0:09:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That warms me up...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.94,0:09:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there it is.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.15,0:09:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so important about the castle?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.07,0:09:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The only doctor in the land, \NDr. Kureha, lives there.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.87,0:09:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,People call her a witch.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.95,0:09:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Of all the places, \Nwhy does it have to be so far away?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.13,0:09:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then call her here right away! \NWe have a critical patient!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.96,0:09:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we wanted to, \Nthere's no way to contact her.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.33,0:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! And she calls herself a doctor?! \NWhat the hell is she like?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.80,0:09:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As a doctor, she's very skilled.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.97,0:09:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's an eccentric old hag. \NShe's nearly 140 years old now.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.05,0:09:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.01,0:09:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,140?! I think {\i1}she{\i0} might need help!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.93,0:09:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And, let's see... \NShe likes pickled plums.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.01,0:09:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens when people \Nhere get sick or injured?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.36,0:09:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She comes down from the \Nmountain when she feels like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.90,0:09:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks for patients, \Ntreats them, then, as payment,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.11,0:09:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,she takes whatever she wants \Nfrom their houses before leaving.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.96,0:10:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like an unfriendly old hag!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.33,0:10:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! She almost sounds like a pirate!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.70,0:10:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But how does such an old \Nwoman go down that mountain?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.67,0:10:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an odd rumor...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.75,0:10:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but several people claim to have seen her
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.96,0:10:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,riding a sleigh through \Nthe sky on moonlit nights...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.80,0:10:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the reason she's called a witch...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.14,0:10:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Some also saw her with a strange \Ncreature they'd never seen before...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.31,0:10:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it! See? It's a Snow Man! \NIt's a snowy mountain, after all!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.57,0:10:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew there'd be one!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.49,0:10:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A witch and a Snow Man?! \NOh, please never let us run into them!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.07,0:10:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She {\i1}is{\i0} the only doctor, but she's \Na hag I'd prefer to stay away from.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.20,0:10:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All we can do is wait for the next \Ntime she comes down the mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.58,0:10:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.00,0:10:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! We can't wait for that! \NEven as we speak, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0} is...!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.27,0:11:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Nami! Nami! Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.09,0:11:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.18,0:11:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! She's awake!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.69,0:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, the only way to see a \Ndoctor is to climb a mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.06,0:11:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna climb it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.15,0:11:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.23,0:11:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be crazy! \NWhat are you doing with Nami?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.40,0:11:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay! I'll carry her on my back!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.11,0:11:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll only make things even worse!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.61,0:11:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the problem? \NWe need to hurry, don't we?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.53,0:11:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, but you can't! \NLook at how steep and tall it is!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.41,0:11:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.46,0:11:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you can make it, \Nbut it'd be too hard on Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.83,0:11:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But, look! \NIf we fall, we'll land in snow!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.05,0:11:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a healthy person would die \Ninstantly after a fall from there!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.51,0:11:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously! \NShe's 6°C over normal temperature!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.26,0:11:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you even get it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.23,0:11:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to get over this fast...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.44,0:11:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to hurry... for Vivi...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.45,0:12:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, Captain!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.33,0:12:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more like it! \NJust leave it to me!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.98,0:12:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it! \NLike captain, like navigator!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.27,0:12:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what condition \Nyou're in, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.65,0:12:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you'll be okay? \NIt'll take hours to get there!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.57,0:12:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Old guy! Meat! Gimme meat!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.40,0:12:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Meat?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.91,0:12:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! I'm comin' too!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.32,0:12:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Luffy! Don't fall even once, \Nor you can expect Nami to die!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.29,0:12:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! Even once?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.12,0:12:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Hold still! \NI need to tie this right!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.92,0:12:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All set.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.17,0:13:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm going to wait here. \NI'd only get in the way.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.34,0:13:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.34,0:13:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.09,0:13:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Nami! Hold on tight!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.85,0:13:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.27,0:13:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're really set on going... \NI won't stop you.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.98,0:13:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least climb up from the other side.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.52,0:13:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There are Lapins on this course.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.43,0:13:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Fierce, carnivorous rabbits.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.85,0:13:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you encounter a pack of them, \Nyou're as good as dead.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.24,0:13:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabbits? But we're in a hurry.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.70,0:13:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be fine. Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.41,0:13:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I'll kick 'em!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.12,0:13:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Kick?! You can't be serious! \NYou'd be walking to your deaths!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.50,0:13:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.75,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then! Let's go, Sanji! \NBefore Nami dies!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.67,0:13:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Don't say things that \Ncould jinx us, you dumbass!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.89,0:13:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they really be all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.72,0:13:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not worried about those two...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.84,0:13:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the question is if Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}'s \Nstrength will last long enough...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.44,0:13:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they make it there safely...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.53,0:14:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.11,0:14:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Come inside. It's cold out.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.70,0:14:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's okay. \NI want to stay outside.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.12,0:14:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, too...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.96,0:14:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.97,0:14:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I will join you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.12,0:14:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We did have some, long ago...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.79,0:14:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.11,0:15:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors. \NBut they're all gone now, for certain reasons.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.75,0:15:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all incredibly skilled...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.92,0:15:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We were even known as an advanced medical nation.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.76,0:15:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.47,0:15:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This country was destroyed \Njust a few months ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.52,0:15:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At the hands of pirates!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.23,0:15:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.23,0:15:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire country?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.31,0:15:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you were so nervous about us?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.15,0:15:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The word "pirate" is still \Ntoo much for everyone to handle...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.53,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.62,0:15:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were only five \Npeople in that pirate group.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.29,0:15:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain called himself "Blackbeard,"
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.79,0:15:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and he destroyed our country \Nin the blink of an eye
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.21,0:15:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with his devastating power...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:47.17,0:15:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Only five pirates?! \NYou can't be serious!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.47,0:15:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Blackbeard?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.02,0:15:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some who say it was \Nactually good for the country.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.76,0:15:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing good about \Na country being destroyed!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.10,0:16:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! \NThat's the stupidest thing I've ever heard!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.64,0:16:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.77,0:16:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But people say that because the \Nmonarchy that existed here until then
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.86,0:16:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,was appalling in the eyes of the citizens.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.03,0:16:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The country's former name was Drum Kingdom!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.45,0:16:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The king's name was Wapol!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.41,0:16:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the worst king possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.08,0:16:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! That man! I remember him!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.00,0:16:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wapol?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.18,0:16:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotten a little colder. \NThe wind's picking up.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.72,0:16:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So why aren't you wearing shoes?! \NJust seeing that is painful!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.06,0:16:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my police!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.81,0:16:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Police?! You mean "policy"!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.40,0:16:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.61,0:16:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, did you know? \NPeople in snowy countries never sleep!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.45,0:16:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.08,0:16:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause they'll die if they go to sleep!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.41,0:17:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid! \NThere's nobody like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.96,0:17:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the truth! \NSomeone told me a long time ago!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.13,0:17:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Usopp, I bet.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.17,0:17:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I heard it in a pub in my village!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.09,0:17:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why did that Dalton guy have a bed?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.97,0:17:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good point.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.60,0:17:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's for when he dies, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.60,0:17:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.02,0:17:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, did you know this?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.77,0:17:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Women in snowy lands all have silky-smooth skin!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.03,0:17:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.12,0:17:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.61,0:17:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever you're cold, \Nyou rub your skin for warmth.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.12,0:17:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get smooth skin.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.58,0:17:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So women in snowy places have \Nsuch silky-smooth, white skin!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.33,0:17:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How come it's white?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.21,0:17:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the color of the \Nconstantly-falling snow dyes their skin!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.84,0:17:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! You're so dumb!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.09,0:18:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you're really anyone to talk!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.39,0:18:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.43,0:18:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...quit being so damn annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.43,0:18:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What was with that guy?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.98,0:18:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}! \NWe're gonna get you to a doctor!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.69,0:18:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The snow's really deep around here...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.99,0:18:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luffy!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.28,0:18:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Run more smoothly! \NYou're gonna make Nami-{\i1}san{\i0} worse!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.79,0:18:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What are these?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.63,0:18:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're white and big, so they're polar bears! \NI'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.51,0:18:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! You know Wapol?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.01,0:18:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't just know him! \NHe's the pirate who attacked our ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.60,0:18:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I got rid of him, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.85,0:18:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do recall him saying something about Drum Kingdom...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.52,0:18:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.65,0:18:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no question about it! \NI remember clearly now!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.57,0:18:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I met him once at a monarch \Nmeeting my father took me to
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.36,0:19:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was very young!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.49,0:19:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Monarch meeting?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.62,0:19:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just who are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.08,0:19:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, uhh, you see...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.33,0:19:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, we met Wapol! \NYesterday, on our way here!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.17,0:19:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday?! Are you sure?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.17,0:19:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's going on, then?! \NHe called himself a pirate, not a king!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.43,0:19:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He must be calling himself that as camouflage.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.32,0:19:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wapol is merely wandering the sea, \Ntrying to return to this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.60,0:19:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people on that ship were \Nkicked out because they were no match
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.61,0:19:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Blackbeard Pirates when they attacked this country?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.40,0:19:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No match? It's not like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.70,0:19:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.83,0:19:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When it happened, \NWapol's army didn't even try to fight!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.79,0:19:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the moment he learned \Nhow strong the pirates were,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.08,0:19:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wapol abandoned the country and \Nwas the very first to flee out to sea!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.59,0:20:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That threw the entire nation into despair.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.63,0:20:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this what the king...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.22,0:20:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what the king of an entire country does?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.43,0:20:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's appalling! \NA king abandoning his people!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.44,0:20:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Vivi...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.60,0:20:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're exactly right.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.81,0:20:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least Wapol's tyranny is finally over.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.78,0:20:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The remaining people on this \Nisland have come together
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.65,0:20:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to create a new country.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.87,0:20:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we most fear right now is Wapol's return...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.75,0:20:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The return of his monarchy.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.59,0:20:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We must avoid that at all costs, \Nwhile people are still feeling unsure!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.79,0:20:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're to create a new, \Npeaceful nation on this island!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.30,0:20:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It jumped!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.23,0:20:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta be kidding me! \NHow can it move like that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.65,0:20:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, a gorilla?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.56,0:20:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No! A polar bear!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.35,0:20:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bunny!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.60,0:21:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who just called it a gorilla...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.65,0:21:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,These must be the Lapins that \NDalton was talking about!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.41,0:21:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This many of them?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.70,0:21:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.16,0:21:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Wapol-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.12,0:21:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Chess? \NDid you find Straw Hat's ship?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.17,0:21:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Wapol-{\i1}sama{\i0}! \NWe've finally returned home!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.05,0:21:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How many months have passed \Nas we've wandered the sea?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.60,0:21:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our homeland! Drum Kingdom!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.10,0:21:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly?!
